{
  "doc_id": "58441",
  "text": "Several marine bacteria previously isolated from the bottom sediments of Algoa Bay in the Eastern Cape of South Africa as part of the culture collections of the Applied and Environmental Microbiology Research Group (AEMREG), University of Fort Hare, Alice, South Africa were screened for bioflocculant production. The composition of the production medium is as described by previous authors [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] and includes the following: 10 g glucose, 1 g peptone, 0.3 g MgSO 4 · 7H 2 O, 5 g K 2 HPO 4 , 2 g KH 2 PO 4 in 1 L filtered sterilized seawater; and the initial pH of the medium was adjusted to 7.0 with NaOH (0.1 M) and HCl (0.1 M). All media solutions were sterilized by autoclaving.",
